# 6. この胸にあるもの

Akito: You and me singing together, Luka...?
Luka: Yes!
Akito: But why...?
Luka: To get you to let your feelings out all at once, of course!
Akito: You're talking about singing from my heart like Ken said, right? But just singing together doesn't seem like...
Luka: Fine, then let's make it a battle! That should be more enticing, no?
Luka: You're not going to run, are you?
Akito: I know what you're doing, and I'd really rather not take the bait...
Akito: (But...)
Akito: (Just based on her instinct, Luka seems to know what it is that I'm missing.)
Akito: Okay, you're on.
Luka: Yay! Thank you, Akito! This'll help me a lot since I'm much better at getting things across with song!
MEIKO: You did have to twist his arm quite a lot.
Luka: That's just how I do things! Oh, would you all mind acting as the judges?
Len: Yeah, sure! I'll be a judge!
Luka: Thank you! Then, let's get started! Who should go first? Me...?
Akito: Yes, that's fine.
Luka: Alright, I'm going to hit the ground running!!
Luka: ♪————!!
Akito: (Luka really is an incredible singer... She's going strong right out the gates.)
Akito: Hm...?
Akito: (This song... I've heard it before somewhere...)
Akito: (Oh, right... This is the one I sang with Toya and the others when we went camping.)
Luka: ♪————!!
Akito: (Why does she seem so happy...? But her smile's kinda infectious.)
Luka: Okay, that seems like a nice way to start! Now, Akito, it's your turn!
Akito: Here I go...!
Akito: ♪————!!
Akito: (The way Luka sang just now was really good.)
Akito: (But what was she trying to tell me...?)
Luka: Oh, not bad! In that case, let's see how you do when we speed things up!
Luka: ♪————!!
Akito: ...!!
Len: Huh? She sounds totally different now!
MEIKO: Yes. But this song's...
Akito: (Yeah...! It's the one I sang when I confronted those guys from Shepard!)
Akito: (So much happened that time...)
Akito: (I managed to break through the ceiling I had felt trapped under before. But I wasn't satisfied with just that...)
Akito: (After that, people started telling me that I reminded them of Taiga or Ken... That gave me a bit of confidence.)
Luka: ♪————!!
Akito: (However, Len's right... She sounds completely different now. Almost like some kind of illusion...)
Akito: (No, wait... There's more to this... I feel something welling up inside of me.)
Akito: (In my chest... What is this...?)
Luka: ♪————! ♪————!
Luka: Whew... Okay, Akito, your turn!
Luka: Tell me what you're feeling! Give me everything you have!
Akito: What I'm feeling...?
Luka: Yes! You've felt and experienced a lot of different emotions up until now. So, let's throw everything we have at each other!
Akito: What I've felt...?
Akito: (What I...felt just now...)
Akito: ♪...————
Luka: Oh, yes! That's it, Akito!
Len: MEIKO! Is it just me, or did Akito sound a little different just now...?
MEIKO: Yes, just a little bit, but...
MEIKO: Okay. Now I see...
Len: Huh? See what?
MEIKO: I think Luka's trying to draw out Akito's feelings in order to free them.
Len: Free them?
MEIKO: Yes.
MEIKO: Whenever Akito sings, he gives off this impression of wanting to get better—to “surpass”.
MEIKO: And there's nothing wrong with that. His unyielding work ethic is the reason why he's been able to grow to this point.
MEIKO: But there may be a myriad of other emotions hiding behind all that.
MEIKO: Giving up fun things to focus on improving. Burying any worries or sadness that cropped up.
MEIKO: Yes, to some degree you need that self-control to keep moving forward. But Akito's done enough of that already.
MEIKO: Now, he needs to take the next step.
MEIKO: He needs to dig deep and rediscover those feelings that have been buried away for so long. He needs to free them and turn them into song.
MEIKO: That's what Luka's trying to teach him. She's trying to make him realize.
MEIKO: I have a feeling that Ken's been thinking the same thing while singing with Akito...
MEIKO: However, he has a special place in Akito's heart. He can't help but tense up in his presence.
MEIKO: But with Luka...
Luka: ♪————————————!!
Akito: (This is so strange...)
Akito: (I can feel all these emotions rising to the surface...)
Akito: (Fun, excitement, regret...)
Ken: Don't worry. You already have everything you need.
Akito: ...! That's it...!
Akito: If I can turn these feelings into song, then...
Luka: Akito! Stooop!
Akito: ...!
Len: Wait, Luka, what's wrong...?! Akito was just about to...!
Luka: Yes, I know what was about to happen...
Luka: But you need to save that for when you sing against Ken.
Luka: Right now, Akito, there are a lot of different emotions swirling around inside of you.
Luka: But you shouldn't be unleashing them on me.
Luka: You need to do that to your hero. You need to do that to Ken!
Akito: Okay, understood.
Akito: I really appreciate it, Luka. I have a much better idea of what I need to do now thanks to you.
Luka: Hehe. I'm glad to hear that!
Luka: Now, go unleash everything you just felt! Pow!
